### Banking Transactions API — sample requests
### Works with the IntelliJ/PhpStorm HTTP Client and the VS Code "REST Client" extension.
### Start the server first:  npm start   (http://localhost:3000)
@host = http://localhost:3000

### Health check
GET {{host}}/health

> {% client.test("ok", () => client.assert(response.status === 200)); %}

### Create a transfer (expect 201) — saves the new id into {{txId}}
POST {{host}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "ACC-12345",
  "toAccount": "ACC-67890",
  "amount": 100.50,
  "currency": "USD",
  "type": "transfer"
}

> {%
  client.test("created", () => client.assert(response.status === 201));
  client.global.set("txId", response.body.id);
%}

### Create a deposit (expect 201) — only toAccount allowed
POST {{host}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "toAccount": "ACC-12345",
  "amount": 500,
  "currency": "USD",
  "type": "deposit"
}

> {% client.test("created", () => client.assert(response.status === 201)); %}

### Create a withdrawal (expect 201) — only fromAccount allowed
POST {{host}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "ACC-12345",
  "amount": 100,
  "currency": "USD",
  "type": "withdrawal"
}

> {% client.test("created", () => client.assert(response.status === 201)); %}

### Validation failure — THIS IS EXPECTED TO RETURN 400
### (negative amount, bad currency, deposit carrying a fromAccount).
### The test below passes when the API correctly rejects it, so the request shows green.
POST {{host}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "ACC-00001",
  "toAccount": "ACC-12345",
  "amount": -5,
  "currency": "XYZ",
  "type": "deposit"
}

> {%
  client.test("rejected with 400", () => client.assert(response.status === 400));
  client.test("has details[]", () => client.assert(Array.isArray(response.body.details)));
%}

### List all transactions
GET {{host}}/transactions

### Filter: by account (matches fromAccount OR toAccount)
GET {{host}}/transactions?accountId=ACC-12345

### Filter: by type
GET {{host}}/transactions?type=transfer

### Filter: by inclusive date range
GET {{host}}/transactions?from=2024-01-01&to=2024-12-31

### Filter: combined
GET {{host}}/transactions?accountId=ACC-12345&type=transfer

### Get one transaction by id — uses {{txId}} captured from the transfer above.
### Run the "Create a transfer" request first so {{txId}} is set.
GET {{host}}/transactions/{{txId}}

> {% client.test("found", () => client.assert(response.status === 200)); %}

### Account balance
GET {{host}}/accounts/ACC-12345/balance

### Account summary (Task 4-A)
GET {{host}}/accounts/ACC-12345/summary

### Simple interest (Task 4-B)
GET {{host}}/accounts/ACC-12345/interest?rate=0.05&days=30

### CSV export (Task 4-C)
GET {{host}}/transactions/export?format=csv

### Rate limiting (Task 4-D): send >100 requests/min from one IP to receive 429
